casebody.data:
Tara Sheneva WILLIAMS
v.
Deborah K. JOHNSON, Acting Warden. No. 13-9085. Supreme Court of the United States July 1, 2014. Kurt David Hermansen, San Diego, CA, Steven M. Klepper, Kramon & Graham, P.A., Baltimore, MD, for Petitioner Tara Sheneva Williams. Stephanie Brenan, Counsel of Record, California Dept. of Justice, Los Angeles, CA, for Respondent Deborah K. Johnson. Prior report: C.A.9, 720 F.3d 1212 . PER CURIAM.

The motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for a writ of certiorari are granted. The judgment of the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit is vacated, and the case is remanded for consideration of petitioner's Sixth Amendment claim under the standard set forth in 28 U.S.C. § 2254 (d).

It is so ordered.
